If you saw my last piece, this one called “I got the bill” will make cents! Donald is waddlin right up to the register to pay for Daisy’s shoe shopping spree. But I’ll let y’all in on a lil secret—he only looks so happy because he’s paying with Uncle Scrooge’s card lolol. Okay hope you enjoyed my story ily bye 😚 For art inquires, send me an email at dom@domcorona.com

We are kicking off our Disney Artist Spotlight series with @domcorona . Dom is a Disney Artist who has been featured in Forbes Magazine, Disney Parks Blogs, and is currently at Festival of the Arts. He first learned to draw Donald Duck in 2008 which propelled him into life as a Disney Artist. He attended the Disney College Program and continues to create with Mickey Mouse as his main source of inspiration. Listen now wherever you get your podcasts.
Here it is — Quack-tose Intolerant! 🍦🎨 You might be thinking “if Donald’s Quack-tose Intolerant, why is he eating ice cream?” Easy answer, it’s not real dairy—it’s bOAT MILK! lololol ok I’m done

Meet Topo Sole & Topo Luna ☀️🌙 Two of my pieces at the forefront of @fsorlando #FSOrlandoXDomCorona

Two pieces come to life, each representing a distinct moment in the magical realm of the Four Seasons Orlando. The first piece, named “Topo Sole,” portrays Mickey basking in the glorious sunshine, relishing a day of leisure at the luxurious resort. With a vibrant smile adorning his face, Mickey finds solace under the warm rays of the sun, indulging in a moment of pure relaxation. The colors of the artwork dance with joy, capturing the essence of Mickey’s carefree spirit. 

Adjacent to “Topo Sole” stands a companion, titled “Topo Luna.” Inspired by the mesmerizing firework chandelier that adorns the lobby of the Four Seasons, this piece portrays Mickey gazing skyward in awe as the night sky erupts into a spectacular display of fireworks at the Magic Kingdom. 

The interplay between “Topo Sole” and “Topo Luna” mirrors the flow of guests, representing their path through the entrance—heading right to retire for the night and left to embrace the adventures of a new day. These Mickey Mouse-terpieces showcase the magic that awaits within the Four Seasons Orlando, where joy, relaxation, and enchantment converge. The captivating character and positioning of the pieces seamlessly transports visitors into a world where imagination soars, promising an unforgettable experience for all who step through the doors.
